Title: ISU, Department of Computer Science
Body: Date: Tue, 26 Nov 1996 23:18:04 GMT Server: Apache/1.1.1 Content-type: text/html ISU, Department of Computer Science Computing activities began at Iowa State in the late 1930's when John Vincent Atanasoff , a professor of physics and mathematics, built a computer on campus that is now recognized as the first electronic digital computer.
